Bruce Kirkpatrick Anderson: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 21, 2017 11:59 PM ET
Capital Markets

Company Overview of Andwel Partners



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Bruce Kirkpatrick Anderson  Owner and Manager, Andwel PartnersAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 4 Board Members in 4 different organizations across 9 different industries.See Board Relationships77--
Background

		Mr. Bruce Kirkpatrick Anderson co-founded Welsh, Carson, Anderson & Stowe (WCAS) and Welsh, Carson, Anderson & Stowe XI, L.P and has been its General Partner since 1979. Mr. Anderson has more than 30 years of experience in the financial services industry. He served as the Chief Financial Officer of TeraView Limited. He was the General Partner and Founder of Welsh, Carson, Anderson & Stowe IV, L.P. He focuses investments on information and business services industry. ... He works at Andwel Partners. He was employed at Welsh, Carson, Anderson & Stowe IV, L.P as General Partner. He served for nine years with Automatic Data Processing, Inc. (ADP) and served as its Executive Vice President and also served as the President of ADP International since August 1978. He served as Secretary at TTP Communications PLC, which he joined in 2000 and served as its Finance Director since August 2000. He served as the President at Amdocs Limited from August 1978 to September 2004. He served as an Acting Group Finance Director of ANT Plc since May 31, 2007. He spent four years in computer marketing with International Business Machines Corporation, or IBM. He served as the Chairman of the Board of Amdocs Limited from September 1997 to October 1, 2011, Comdata Holdings Corp. from March 1987 to March 1992. He also serves as a Director at Genicom Corporation, Broadway & Seymour, Inc. and several privately held companies. He has been an Independent Director of Alliance Data Systems Corp. since August 1996. He serves as a Director of Broadcast UK Ltd., RadioScape Ltd., Instantlabs Medical Diagnostics Corporation and docs Limited. He served as a Director of Headstrong Inc., Automatic Data Processing, Inc., MedEView, Inc. and The Cerplex Group, Inc. He served as a Director at Fiserv, Inc. from February 19, 2004 to February 16 2005 and also previously served as a Director from 1984 to 1996. He served as an Executive Director of TTP Communications plc. He served as a Director of ANT Plc from January 2008 to May 21, 2009, Amdocs Limited from September 1997 to November 6, 2012, Seer Technologies, Inc., since July 1994 and Comdata Holdings Corporation since 1987. He qualified as a Fellow of the Chartered Institute of Management Accountants while working with Coopers and Lybrand. Mr. Anderson has a BA in Modern Languages from University of Minnesota in 1962 and an M Sc. in Management and Business Studies from Warwick University.Read Full Background




